title: Title of Minister) Order 2023 (S.I. No. 19 of 2023)), hereby order as follows:
heading: 4. No fee shall be payable to Tailte Éireann in respect of an application to
text_raw:
4. No fee shall be payable to Tailte Éireann in respect of an application to 
it for the registration of an entry of a charge created in accordance with section 
62 of the Act of 1964 on the register (within the meaning of the Act of 1964) 
that – 

(a) 

(b) 

is lodged by electronic means in a manner approved by Tailte 
Éireann, and 

complies with any requirements specified by Tailte Éireann in 
respect of an application for such registration. 

#Notice of the making of this Statutory Instrument was published in 
"Iris Oifigiúil" of 22nd December, 2023. 

 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 The Minister for Public Expenditure, National Development Plan Delivery and 
Reform consents to the making of the foregoing Order. 

[677] 3 

GIVEN under the Official Seal of the Minister for Public 
Expenditure, National Development Plan Delivery and 
Reform, 

20 December, 2023. 

PASCHAL DONOHOE, 

Minister for Public Expenditure, National Development 
Plan Delivery and Reform. 

GIVEN under my Official Seal, 

20 December, 2023. 

DARRAGH O’BRIEN, 

Minister for Housing, Local Government and Heritage.
